    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI set my monitor to 125% scaling. After upgrading from 0.12.0-2536 to 0.12.0-2654, the intro message no longer displays at 125% nor does it display at 150% or 175% either. However, it does display at 100% scaling. When running the :intro command, the message will display at 125%. Upgrading to the lastest nightly, 0.12.0-2702, did not fix the issue.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/00482d26-a851-41c4-8277-83726b362b15\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nOn latest nightly, run nvim --clean.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe intro message displays at 125% scaling.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-2702+g40a42affa5\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.2.125\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11 25H2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20260117-154428-05343b38\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nscoop ",
